@startuml
title The structure of ISO 20022
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #E9EDF5
  BorderColor #26386B
}
skinparam package {
  BackgroundColor #F4F6FA
  BorderColor #26386B
}
skinparam ArrowColor #26386B

package "The standard" {
  [Methodology\n(how messages are designed)] as MET
  [Central dictionary\n(reusable business concepts)] as DIC
  [Syntax\n(XML, JSON, ASN.1)] as SYN
}
[Business message\ne.g. pacs.008, camt.053, sese.023] as MSG
[Business Application Header\n(head.001) envelope] as BAH

MET --> DIC : governs
DIC --> MSG : concepts assembled into
SYN --> MSG : serialised as
BAH --> MSG : wraps and routes
@enduml
